Conduction of workshops on synergies issues of MEA on chemicals is planned.  Development of proposals for organization of the system of information and education on the implementation and decision-making upon conventions are planned.
Planned in future reporting cycles in the following manner:

- Organization of a series of workshops on the synergies between chemical related MEAs;

- Development of proposals for organization of the system of information and education on the implementation and decision-making of the three chemical Conventions;

- Development of a long-term plan for national reporting provision and proposals to change the national statistical systems, as well as industry reporting;

- Development of proposals for the institutional structure of state bodies and organizations responsible for the implementation of the conventions and facilitating the creation of such a structure;

99,704 ha (3,3% of ecological zone) as in the baseline
The following works have been initiated/completed by the project to ensure the achievement of the EoP target:

-works were performed on land plots of 152,000 ha total to establish the “Ile-Balkhash” nature reservat. The feasibility study (TEO) was approved by the authorized body, report on the  positive state ecological appraisal was obtained;

-Draft Decree of RK Government on expansion of the “Altyn Yemel” State National Nature Park’s area at 146,500 ha is being approved by concerned authorities;

- field studies on habitation of rare ungulate species of animals of Altyn Yemel and Ile-Balkhash PAs were conducted. Habitation and animal migration maps were drawn for three routes with total length of 664 km. The results of scientific works will be used  for establishment of the  proposed ecological corridor;

-the work on the ENO development for PA establishment in Arganaty plot is being performed. The current status of mountain-valley desert ecosystems of the Ile-Balkhash project area was assessed.

Data reported:

1.Technical economic background report or TEO to establish the “Ile-Balkhash” nature reservat;

2. Draft Decree of RK Government on expansion of the “Altyn Yemel” National Park;

3. Assessment of wildlife condition and migratory routes.
